Oxfam Novib is one of the 17 national affiliates of the Oxfam International Confederation. Oxfam started life in 1956 as the Netherlands Organisation for International Assistance (Novib), and joined forces with Oxfam in 1994.
Working together in confederation, the Oxfam affiliates can speak with one clear and compelling voice on issues of global concern: climate change, health and education for all, agriculture, trade, and conflicts and emergencies. Oxfam Novib focus on these rights:
The right to the resources for a sustainable livelihood
The right to basic social services The right to life and security
The right to social and political participation
The right to an identity
Oxfam Novib a défini dans sa stratégie 2012-2015 au Sénégal de travailler en partenariat avec les Organisations de la société civile sur des thématiques liées au moyens de subsistance durables, l#Education et à la participation politique.
